text: William Shieh is an electrical engineer at the University of Melbourne in Glen Waverley, Victoria, Australia. He was named a Fellow of the Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers in 2013 for his contributions to coherent optical orthogonal frequency-division multiplexing. He was also made a Fellow of the Optical Society. == References == Category:Fellow Members of the IEEE Category:Living people Category:Australian electrical engineers Category:University of Melbourne faculty Category:Fellows of the Optical Society Category:Year of birth missing (living people)
